1. on gitlab, create a project with no README file -- this creates an empty remote repository, and allows us to very easily import our own, local git repository (without any comflict or need to merge/pull)
2. go to a new directory, with the files to back up (delete .git directory by rm -rf .git, if it exists)
3. use the following commands

git config --global user.name "Yuhan Guo"
git config --global user.email "yuhan.guo@cern.ch"
git init
git remote add origin THE_SSH_ADDRESS_OF_THE_REMOTE_REPOSITORY
git add .
git commit -m "Initial commit"
git push -u origin master